        <briefdescription>
<para>Extracts an HDF5 object into an in-memory &quot;blob.&quot; This function uses the HDF5 &quot;CORE&quot; Virtual File Driver (VFD) to create a virtual file in RAM. It then copies an object (dataset or group) from the physical file into this virtual file. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>name</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The name of the object to extract. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>hdf5_blob A handle (hid_t) to the new in-memory HDF5 file image. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
