          <type><ref refid="hdf5__utils_8h_1abbd4e0ea8441a4a391c88ed0688689dc" kindref="member">hdf5_blob</ref></type>
          <declname>blob</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Deallocates the in-memory HDF5 blob and releases system RAM. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Because the blob was created using the H5FD_CORE driver, the &quot;file&quot; exists entirely in a memory buffer. Calling this function tells the HDF5 library that the buffer is no longer needed, effectively performing a &apos;free()&apos; operation on that block of memory.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>blob</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The handle (hid_t) to the in-memory HDF5 file image. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>0 on success, or a negative error code on failure. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
